            <div class="Facts">
                <h3>What is?</h3>
                <p>  
                    Babi Guling is a traditional Balinese dish renowned for its succulent roasted pork. 
                    Prepared by seasoning a whole pig with a blend of local spices like turmeric, garlic, 
                    ginger, and lemongrass, it's then slow-roasted over open flames or in a pit until the skin 
                    becomes crispy and golden, while the meat inside remains tender and flavorful. Served with 
                    accompaniments such as steamed rice, lawar (a Balinese vegetable salad), and sambal matah 
                    (a spicy chili relish), Babi Guling offers a symphony of textures and flavors that exemplify 
                    the vibrant culinary heritage of Bali.
                </p>
